The paper presents a formulation of grid-based graph representation problems as an integer linear program (ILP) and a corresponding SAT instance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with optimization problems, such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper mentions solving NP-hard graph problems, which could also place it in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
